BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_1_pt3
BaseField.Text: All staff shall have a working knowledge of the operating procedures.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_16_hd
BaseField.Text: Reporting of Abuse, Neglect, and Deaths.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_004_16_
BaseField.Text: Providers shall adhere to the statutory requirements for reporting abuse, neglect, and deaths of children under chapter 39, F.S., and of adults under sections 415.1034 and 397.501(7)(c), F.S.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_5_pt1
BaseField.Text: Education of staff in the importance of the grievance system

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0045_1__a_5_pt2
BaseField.Text: Education of staff in the importance of individual rights;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046
BaseField.Text: Staff Training, Qualifications, and Scope of Practice.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1_pt1
BaseField.Text: Providers shall develop and implement a staff development plan.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1_pt2
BaseField.Text: At least one (1) staff member with skill in developing staff training plans shall be assigned the responsibility of ensuring that staff development activities are implemented.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__a_
BaseField.Text: The staff development plan must be reviewed at least annually through the quality assurance program and revised as needed. The plan must be signed and dated.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__b_
BaseField.Text: All required training activities shall be documented and accessible for Department review, including the date, duration, topic, name(s) of participants, and name(s) of the trainer or training organization.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_
BaseField.Text: Within six (6) months of the hiring date, employees must complete the following trainings:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_1_
BaseField.Text: A two (2) hour educational course on HIV/AIDS as required by section 381.0035, F.S.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_2_
BaseField.Text: Overdose prevention training which must be renewed biennially. The training shall include, at a minimum, information about:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_2_c_
BaseField.Text: Naloxone, the medication that reverses opioid overdose, including how to use Naloxone and the importance of individuals at risk of opioid overdose and their friends and family having access to Naloxone.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_3_pt1
BaseField.Text: Training in incident reporting procedures and requirements in accordance with subsection 65D-30.004(17), F.A.C., the affirmative duty requirements

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_3_pt2
BaseField.Text: Training in the affirmative duty requirements and protections of chapter 415, F.S.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_3_pt3
BaseField.Text: Training in Title V of the Americans with Disabilities Act.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_4_pt1
BaseField.Text: For direct care staff working in component services identified in subsection 65D-30.004(12), F.A.C.,

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_4_pt2
BaseField.Text: two (2) hours of training in verbal de-escalation techniques

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_5_
BaseField.Text: Staff performing nursing support functions must be trained in those services prior to performing that function.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__c_6_
BaseField.Text: For all direct care staff, training and certification in cardiopulmonary resuscitation (CPR) and first aid. Staff must maintain CPR and first aid certification, and a copy of the valid certificate must be filed in the personnel record.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_pt1
BaseField.Text: All staff and volunteers who provide direct care or prevention services shall participate in a minimum of 10 hours of documented training per year related to their duties and responsibilities.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_pt2
BaseField.Text: This includes training conducted annually in the following areas:

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_1_
BaseField.Text: Prevention and control of infection in inpatient and residential settings;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_2_
BaseField.Text: Fire prevention, life safety, and disaster preparedness;

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__d_5_
BaseField.Text: Federal law, 42 CFR, Part 2, and sections 397.334(10), 397.501(7), 397.752, F.S. applicable state laws regarding confidentiality.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__e_
BaseField.Text: In instances where an individual has received the requisite training as required in paragraphs (1)(c) and (d) during the year prior to employment by a provider, that individual will have met the training requirements. This provision applies only if the individual is able to produce documentation that the training was completed and that such training was provided by persons who or organizations that are qualified to provide such training

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__f_hd
BaseField.Text: Special Training Requirements for Clinical Staff.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__f_
BaseField.Text: All new clinical staff who work at least 20 hours per week or more must receive 12 hours of competency-based training related to substance use disorder treatment and recovery within the first year.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_0046_1__g_
BaseField.Text: In addition to paragraphs (1)(c) and (d), new staff providing prevention services shall receive 12 hours basic training in science-based prevention within the first year of employment.

BaseField.Name: CIT_65D_30_006_4__e_
BaseField.Text: All direct services staff working in outpatient detoxification shall be trained in the outpatient detoxification protocol prior to having contact with the individual in need of services.
